  188: init_per_testcase(Func, Config) ->
  189:     CaseDir = filename:join(proplists:get_value(priv_dir, Config), Func),
  190:     ok = filelib:ensure_dir(filename:join([CaseDir, dummy_file])),
  191:     true = code:add_patha(CaseDir),
  192:     [{case_dir, CaseDir}|Config].
  193: 
  194: end_per_testcase(_Func, Config) ->
  195:     CaseDir = proplists:get_value(case_dir, Config),
  196:     unload_modules(CaseDir),
  197:     asn1_test_lib:rm_dirs([CaseDir]),
  198:     code:del_path(CaseDir).
  199: 
  200: unload_modules(CaseDir) ->
  201:     F = fun(Name0, Acc) ->
  202:                 Name1 = filename:rootname(filename:basename(Name0)),
  203:                 Name = list_to_existing_atom(Name1),
  204:                 [Name|Acc]
  205:         end,
  206:     Beams1 = lists:usort(filelib:fold_files(CaseDir, "[.]beam\$", true, F, [])),
  207:     Beams = [M || M <- Beams1, code:is_loaded(M) =/= false],
  208:     _ = [begin
  209:              code:purge(M),
  210:              code:delete(M),
  211:              code:purge(M),
  212:              io:format("Unloaded ~p", [M])
  213:          end || M <- Beams],
  214:     ok.

  216: %%------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  217: %% Test runners
  218: %%------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  219: 
  220: test(Config, TestF) ->
  221:     test(Config, TestF, [per, uper, ber, jer, {ber,[ber,jer]}]).
  222: 
  223: test(Config, TestF, Rules) ->
  224:     Fun = fun(C, R, O) ->
  225:                   M = element(2, erlang:fun_info(TestF, module)),
  226:                   F = element(2, erlang:fun_info(TestF, name)),
  227:                   io:format("Running ~p:~p with ~p...~n", [M, F, {R, O}]),
  228:                   try
  229:                       TestF(C, R, O)
  230:                   catch
  231:                       Class:Reason:Stk ->
  232:                           NewReason = {Reason, [{rule, R}, {options, O}]},
  233:                           erlang:raise(Class, NewReason, Stk)
  234:                   end
  235:           end,
  236:     Result = [run_case(Config, Fun, rule(Rule), opts(Rule)) || Rule <- Rules],
  237:     case lists:usort(Result) of
  238:         [true|_Skips] -> true; % At least one test ran
  239:         Skips        -> {skip, [R || {skip, R} <- Skips]} % All skipped
  240:     end.
  241: 
  242: rule(A) when is_atom(A) -> A;
  243: rule({A, _Opts} )       -> A.
  244: 
  245: opts(Rule) when is_atom(Rule) -> [];
  246: opts({_Rule, Opts})         -> Opts.
  247: 
  248: run_case(Config, Fun, Rule, Opts) ->
  249:     CaseDir = proplists:get_value(case_dir, Config),
  250:     Dir = filename:join([CaseDir, join(Rule, Opts)]),
  251:     ok = filelib:ensure_dir(filename:join([Dir, dummy_file])),
  252:     replace_path(CaseDir, Dir),
  253:     NewConfig = lists:keyreplace(case_dir, 1, Config, {case_dir, Dir}),
  254: 
  255:     % Run the actual test function
  256:     Result = Fun(NewConfig, Rule, Opts),
  257: 
  258:     replace_path(Dir, CaseDir),
  259:     case Result of
  260:         {skip, _Reason} -> Result;
  261:         _               -> true
  262:     end.
  263: 
  264: replace_path(PathA, PathB) ->
  265:     true = code:del_path(PathA),
  266:     true = code:add_patha(PathB).
  267: 
  268: join(Rule, Opts) ->
  269:     lists:join("_", [atom_to_list(Rule)|lists:map(fun atom_to_list/1, Opts)]).

  275: %% Cover run-time functions that are only called by the ASN.1 compiler
  276: %% (if any).
  277: cover(_) ->
  278:     Wc = filename:join([code:lib_dir(asn1),"ebin","asn1ct_eval_*.beam"]),
  279:     Beams = filelib:wildcard(Wc),
  280:     true = Beams =/= [],
  281:     [begin
  282: 	 M0 = filename:basename(Beam),
  283: 	 M1 = filename:rootname(M0),
  284: 	 M = list_to_atom(M1),
  285: 	 "asn1ct_eval_" ++ Group0 = M1,
  286: 	 Group = list_to_atom(Group0),
  287: 	 io:format("%%\n"
  288: 		   "%% ~s\n"
  289: 		   "%%\n", [M]),
  290: 	 asn1ct_func:start_link(),
  291: 	 [asn1ct_func:need({Group,F,A}) ||
  292: 	     {F,A} <- M:module_info(exports), F =/= module_info],
  293: 	 asn1ct_func:generate(group_leader())
  294:      end || Beam <- Beams],
  295:     ok.

  584: constraint_equivalence_abs(Config) ->
  585:     DataDir = proplists:get_value(data_dir, Config),
  586:     CaseDir = proplists:get_value(case_dir, Config),
  587:     Asn1Spec = "ConstraintEquivalence",
  588:     Asn1Src = filename:join(DataDir, Asn1Spec),
  589:     ok = asn1ct:compile(Asn1Src, [abs,{outdir,CaseDir}]),
  590:     AbsFile = filename:join(CaseDir, Asn1Spec++".abs"),
  591:     {ok,Terms} = file:consult(AbsFile),
  592:     Cs = [begin
  593: 	      Constraints = element(4, Type),
  594: 	      Name1 = atom_to_list(Name0),
  595: 	      {Name,_} = lists:splitwith(fun(C) -> C =/= $X end, Name1),
  596: 	      {Name,Constraints}
  597: 	  end || {typedef,_,_,Name0,Type} <- Terms],
  598:     R = sofs:relation(Cs, [{name,constraint}]),
  599:     F0 = sofs:relation_to_family(R),
  600:     F = sofs:to_external(F0),
  601:     Diff = [E || {_,L}=E <- F, length(L) > 1],
  602:     case Diff of
  603: 	[] ->
  604: 	    ok;
  605: 	[_|_] ->
  606: 	    io:put_chars("Not equivalent:\n"),
  607: 	    [io:format("~s: ~p\n", [N,D]) || {N,D} <- Diff],
  608: 	    ct:fail(length(Diff))
  609:     end.

 1378: xref(_Config) ->
 1379:     S = ?FUNCTION_NAME,
 1380:     xref:start(S),
 1381:     xref:set_default(S, [{verbose,false},{warnings,false},{builtins,true}]),
 1382:     Test = filename:dirname(code:which(?MODULE)),
 1383:     {ok,_PMs} = xref:add_directory(S, Test),
 1384:     Q = "X - XU - \".*_SUITE\" : Mod",
 1385:     UnusedExports = xref:q(S, Q),
 1386:     xref:stop(S),
 1387:     case UnusedExports of
 1388: 	{ok,[]} ->
 1389: 	    ok;
 1390: 	{ok,[_|_]=Res} ->
 1391: 	    ct:fail("Exported, but unused: ~p\n", [Res])
 1392:     end.

 1397: xref_export_all(_Config) ->

 1400:     xref:set_default(S, [{verbose,false},{warnings,false},{builtins,true}]),
 1401:     {ok,_PMs} = xref:add_module(S, code:which(?MODULE)),
 1402:     AllCalled = all_called(),
 1403:     Def = "Called := " ++ lists:flatten(io_lib:format("~p", [AllCalled])),
 1404:     {ok,_} = xref:q(S, Def),
 1405:     {ok,Unused} = xref:q(S, "X - Called - range (closure E | Called)"),
 1406:     xref:stop(S),
 1407:     case Unused -- [{?MODULE,otp_14440_decode,0}] of

 1409:             ok;

 1411:             Msg = [io_lib:format("~p:~p/~p\n", [M,F,A]) || {M,F,A} <- Unused],
 1412:             ct:fail("There are unused functions:\n\n~s\n", [Msg])
